wikipedia_page.main: Eli Small (born 1767 at Petersfield, Hampshire; died 20 May 1837 at Petersfield]) was an English professional cricketer who made 2 known appearances in first-class cricket matches from 1788 to 1796.  He was a son of John Small and brother of Jack Small.

response: He and John Nyren were close friends and Nyren always refers to Small junior as Jack Small. His  younger brother, Eli Small, played for Hampshire.
